title: Navy Jet Crashes Off Key West, Two Crew Members Killed
text:
WASHINGTONâ€”A U.S. Navy jet fighter crashed Wednesday off the coast of Key West, Fla., killing its two crew members.
The F/A-18 Super Hornet was approaching land at the naval air station at about 4:30 p.m. Eastern time. It crashed into the water about a mile east of the runway.
